# Web performance (mandatory)

When **matched files are in context**, read and follow `.cursor/skills/stratezik-web-performance/SKILL.md` before finishing.

## Hard rules (check:release-gates enforces)

1. **App.tsx** — no static imports of `WorldCanvas`, `Loader`, `CustomCursor`, `MoveCounterHUD`, or `SmoothScroll`. Use lazy `DesktopExperience` + `MobileScrollShell`.
2. **Blog** — metadata in `postsMeta.ts`; dynamic article imports only in `postLoaders.ts`. `pageSeoRegistry.ts` imports `postsMeta` only.
3. **Build** — run `npm run build` after shell changes; do not hand users “run build yourself” for perf work.
4. **CSS** — preserve deferred main bundle pattern in `optimize-critical-css.ts`; do not reintroduce blocking `<link rel="stylesheet" href="/assets/index-…">`.
5. **Homepage** — keep above-fold eager; below-fold via `LazyWhenVisible` unless explicitly scoped otherwise.

Pair with **`stratezik-seo-master`** when changes also affect prerender, sitemap, or registry.
